 Review comment:
   this read will result in a race from multiple goroutines
   
   The guarantee of using `atomic.AddInt64(&b.refCount -1) == 0` is only one goroutine will pass into the block
   
   We _could_ update `Release()` to return an `int` which is the current reference count after the call to `Release`, which would resolve the problem. This is a pattern used in other languages using reference counting:
   
   ```go
   if b.builder.Release() == 0 {
       if b.data != nil {
           // ...
       }
   }
   ```

