 Review comment:
   I agree, it may be better just to leave the code, however, if the `builder.Release` method returns the new reference count:
   
   ```go
    // Release decreases the reference count by 1.
    // When the reference count goes to zero, the memory is freed.
    func (b *builder) Release() int64 {
    	debug.Assert(atomic.LoadInt64(&b.refCount) > 0, "too many releases")
   
    	newref := atomic.AddInt64(&b.refCount, -1)
    	if newref == 0 {
    		if b.nullBitmap != nil {
    			b.nullBitmap.Release()
    			b.nullBitmap = nil
    		}
    	}
    	return newref
    }
   ```
   
   it is the equivalent of
   
   ```go
   if atomic.AddInt64(&b.refCount -1) == 0 {
       b.data != nil {
   ```

